register.description: These registers are used to control functionality of CPUs without JTAG ports. There can be upto 32 of these registers

bitfield.description: Reserved, returns 0
Core is in retention mode
Sticky bit indicating a reset has occured Write 1 to clear this bit
Power Loss Detected Sticky bit, write a 1 to clear this bit
Inhinit Sleep Block core from entering sleep mode
Core debug logic is powered
Unnatural Reset Device reset state is being affected by debug logic
Writing a 1 releases the WIR When read this returns the reset status, 1 indicates core is in reset
Reset Mode 0=normal, 1=WIR, 2=Blk Rst, 3=Blk Assert, 4=Halt on Rst, 5=Cancel, 6=Halt and Block, 7=Halt-Blk-assert
Debug Enabled signal to the core
Reserved, return 0
Writing this bit causes Execution Read will return the Debug Attention input value
Reserved, returns 0 when read
The core wants to turn off it's power when high
Reserved, returns 0 when read
Core is powered up when high
The core wants to turn off it's clock when high
Force core active Turn on power and clocks
When high the core clock is active
Security bit When high security is allowing access
The core controlled by this register exists when 1
